{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\nOnce the generated CLI and MCP references exist, trim the duplicated, volatile\ncommand/tool/config catalogs out of `README.md` and replace them with links to the\ngenerated references. Keep the README focused on what rebar is, install, the tested\nquickstart, and routing links. This reduces the README's maintenance surface without\ngutting the front door.\n\nSequenced AFTER the CLI/MCP reference generators land (this ticket `depends_on` them)\nso the README points at real generated pages rather than removing content with no\nreplacement.\n\n## Scope\n- Identify command/tool/config catalogs in `README.md` now covered by generated\n  references and replace them with a short pointer + link.\n- Preserve the narrative front-door content (what/why, install, tested quickstart,\n  routing).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Volatile catalogs duplicated from the generated references are removed from\n      `README.md` and replaced with a short pointer + link to `docs/cli-reference.md`\n      and `docs/mcp-reference.md` (verify, prints nothing):\n      `grep -qF '(docs/cli-reference.md)' README.md && grep -qF '(docs/mcp-reference.md)' README.md || echo \"MISSING REF LINK\"`\n- [ ] The CLI COMMAND CATALOG (the fenced block that listed ~28 `rebar <cmd>` lines\n      under `## CLI`) is genuinely GONE, not merely re-linked — DETERMINISTIC checks\n      (both print nothing): the README no longer holds a dense command listing\n      `[ \"$(grep -cE '^rebar [a-z]' README.md)\" -le 10 ] || echo \"CATALOG STILL PRESENT\"`\n      AND the README got shorter `[ \"$(wc -l < README.md)\" -lt 628 ] || echo \"NOT TRIMMED\"`.\n      (Recalibrated from the original `<=500` proxy, which wrongly assumed ~165 lines of\n      duplicated catalog; the genuine CLI-command catalog was ~28 lines — the rest of\n      `## CLI` is conceptual narrative that must be KEPT, per \"don't gut the front door\".\n      See the recalibration comment on this ticket.)\n- [ ] The README retains ALL its front-door narrative sections (what/why, install,\n      quickstart) — each heading still exists (verify, prints nothing):\n      `for h in '## Why rebar' '## How it works' '## Install' '## Quickstart'; do grep -qF \"$h\" README.md || echo \"LOST $h\"; done`\n      (replaces the subjective \"stands alone\" with concrete required-section checks that\n      cover the scope-required what/why + front-door content.)\n- [ ] No dead relative links in README — self-contained proof (prints nothing):\n      `grep -oE ']\\(([^)]+)\\)' README.md | sed -E 's/^]\\(|\\)$//g' | grep -E '^(\\./)?[^:#]+\\.md' | while read L; do f=$(printf '%s' \"$L\" | sed 's/#.*//'); [ -f \"$f\" ] || [ -f \"$(dirname README.md)/$f\" ] || echo \"DEAD: $L\"; done`\n      This is self-contained and does not depend on any CI gate existing. Sibling `f088`\n      (this ticket `depends_on` it) adds the CI docs-link gate that keeps it enforced;\n      b5a4 lands AFTER f088, so the gate exists in CI when this change lands.\n\nFiles: `README.md`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783832454294253001,"uuid":"d7ea9191-028b-4311-9f91-7e4cd9b941ee"}